cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper proposes a formulation for efficient exploration in sensorimotor learning, which involves training an ensemble of dynamics models and incentivizing the agent to explore in a self-supervised manner without external reward. This formulation is demonstrated across a variety of benchmark environments including stochastic-Atari, Mujoco, Unity, and a real robot. Given the focus on machine learning and robotics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves visual environments, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and control theory suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control).
